The President has signed two bills into law: H.R. 1321, the "Microbead-Free Waters Act of 2015," which bans the manufacture and sale of rinse-off cosmetics containing plastic microbeads, and S. 2425, the "Patient Access and Medicare Protection Act," which makes changes to Medicare payments for certain rehabilitation technology and radiation therapy services, provides flexibility in applying a hardship exception from meaningful use of electronic health records, and improves Medicare and Medicaid program integrity.